{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:song-of-solomon.1",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
    "chapterNumber": 1,
    "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 1",
    "summary": "Source text for Song of Solomon 1 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:song-of-solomon.1.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 1:1",
      "text": "The Song of Songs, which is Solomon's.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:song-of-solomon.1.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 1:2",
      "text": "O that you would kiss me with the kisses of your mouth! For your love is better than wine,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:song-of-solomon.1.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 1:3",
      "text": "your anointing oils are fragrant, your name is oil poured out; therefore the maidens love you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:song-of-solomon.1.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 1:4",
      "text": "Draw me after you, let us make haste. The king has brought me into his chambers. We will exult and rejoice in you; we will extol your love more than wine; rightly do they love you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:song-of-solomon.1.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 1:5",
      "text": "I am very dark, but comely, O daughters of Jerusalem, like the tents of Kedar, like the curtains of Solomon.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:song-of-solomon.1.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 1:6",
      "text": "Do not gaze at me because I am swarthy, because the sun has scorched me. My mother's sons were angry with me, they made me keeper of the vineyards; but, my own vineyard I have not kept!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:song-of-solomon.1.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 1:7",
      "text": "Tell me, you whom my soul loves, where you pasture your flock, where you make it lie down at noon; for why should I be like one who wanders beside the flocks of your companions?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:song-of-solomon.1.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 1:8",
      "text": "If you do not know, O fairest among women, follow in the tracks of the flock, and pasture your kids beside the shepherds' tents.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:song-of-solomon.1.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 1:9",
      "text": "I compare you, my love, to a mare of Pharaoh's chariots.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:song-of-solomon.1.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 1:10",
      "text": "Your cheeks are comely with ornaments, your neck with strings of jewels.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:song-of-solomon.1.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 1:11",
      "text": "We will make you ornaments of gold, studded with silver.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:song-of-solomon.1.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 1:12",
      "text": "While the king was on his couch, my nard gave forth its fragrance.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:song-of-solomon.1.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 1:13",
      "text": "My beloved is to me a bag of myrrh, that lies between my breasts.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:song-of-solomon.1.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 1:14",
      "text": "My beloved is to me a cluster of henna blossoms in the vineyards of En-gedi.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:song-of-solomon.1.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 1:15",
      "text": "Behold, you are beautiful, my love; behold, you are beautiful; your eyes are doves.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:song-of-solomon.1.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 1:16",
      "text": "Behold, you are beautiful, my beloved, truly lovely. Our couch is green;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:song-of-solomon.1.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "song-of-solomon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Song of Solomon 1:17",
      "text": "the beams of our house are cedar, our rafters are pine.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
